[2
Date: Thu, 20 Jul 2000 23:38:11 +0600
From: "Manjur A. Chowdhury" <alpha@dhaka.agni.com>

Dengue in Dhaka up-date, 20 Jul 2000
---------------------------------------
A significant number of dengue cases have been reported during the last two
weeks in Dhaka, Bangladesh. So far, seven persons died out of estimated
four hundred reported dengue cases. Two vector mosquito species (_Aedes
aegypti_ and _Ae. albopictus_) have been recorded in significant numbers in
Dhaka city area. The Breteau Index of _Aedes_ was recorded to be 138 in a
recent survey (July, 2000). In 1997, the Breteau Index was recorded to be
30.8 [mosquito-positive containers per 100 premises - Mod.ES
The government has acted promptly and already formed a high powered
committee to monitor the situation. Dhaka City Corporation which has the
responsibility of controlling mosquitoes has launched a media campaign to
raise the level of awareness among the general public about the importance
of larval control in discarded cans, pots, tyres, etc. The Zoological
Society of Bangladesh and Safeway Pest Control, a local R&D oriented pest
control firm, recently have organized a discussion meeting to review the
dengue situation in Dhaka. So far, no dengue case has been reported from
other cities of Bangladesh.

--
Manjur A. Chowdhury, Ph.D.
Safeway Pest Control
Banani, Dhaka
Bangladesh
<alpha@dhaka.agni.com>
