[4
Date: Fri, 21 Jul 2000 12:20:02 -0400
From: Marjorie P. Pollack <pollackmp@mindspring.com>
Source: ITAR/TASS News Agency: Asia news digest, filed 21 Jul 2000 10:36 AM
EST [edited

Dengue outbreak in Bangladeshi capital
--------------------------------------
Tropical fever has affected hundreds of people and killed 11 of them in
Dhaka, the capital of Bangladesh, in July. "The fever is spreading at an
appalling rate and threatens to evolve into an epidemic," doctors at the
Mujib university clinic said. More than 400 people infected with the
disease are now in hospitals, and the administration of the capital with a
population of nine million has formed task forces to spray insecticides
against infection-carrying mosquitoes in the streets.
