[5
Date: Tue, 18 Jul 2000 11:38:38 GMT
From: M. Cosgriff <mcosgriff@hotmail.com>
Source: Times of India, Tue,18 Jul 2000 04:38:38 -0700 [edited

Dhaka in grip of dengue fever
-----------------------------
Potentially fatal dengue fever is spreading at an alarming rate in Dhaka,
killing eight and putting at least 100 people in hospitals in less than
two weeks, The Independent daily reported on Monday. At the Dhaka Medical
College Hospital, 35 patients are being treated, while another 90 were
reported to have been taken to Shishu hospital. However, doctors at Shishu
confirmed treating only 20 patients. Earlier last week at Birdem, a major
hospital for diabetics, 31 people were brought in to be treated, causing
alarm the disease could have reached epidemic levels. Nazrul Islam, an
expert on virology at the Bangabandhu Sheikh Mujib Medical University and
Hospital warned that unless the spread of the mosquito - which carries the
disease - was checked, the situation could be worse next year. Last year,
46 cases of dengue were detected in Dhaka of which 10 were fatal.
--
