[The Xinhua report mentions that around 60 percent of 500 patients have
been tested positive but does not mention what testing has been reported,
whether testing has consisted of paired sera or single serum samples.
Readers should be reminded that there was a major epidemic of dengue fever
in Dhaka last year, peaking in the period September to November. More
information on the current outbreak would be very much appreciated,
including the age distribution of cases, and hemorrhagic cases, as well as
information on which serotype of dengue is prevalent. As indicated in the
report from Maj. Chowdhury, during the winter months of this year [December
through March 2000, the Dhaka City Corporation was making significant
efforts to control mosquitoes in Dhaka City, with daily rounds of mosquito
fogging activities, and educational campaigns for breeding site reduction.
If there is anyone out there with information on the assessment of the
impact of these activities, please share it with us. Mods.MPP/CP
............................jw/mpp/cp/es
